Completion:

\[ \frac{1}{3} \times \text{Initial volume} = \frac{1}{3} \times 16 \]

\[ \text{Initial volume} = 16 \times \frac{3}{1} \]

\[ \text{Initial volume} = 48 \text{ gallons} \]

Now, to fill the tank, 16 gallons of water are added. The total volume the tank holds will be the initial volume plus the 16 gallons:

\[ \text{Total volume} = \text{Initial volume} + 16 \]

\[ \text{Total volume} = 48 + 16 \]

\[ \text{Total volume} = 64 \text{ gallons} \]

Therefore, the tank will hold 64 gallons of water when full. 

#### 64 GALLONS.

The total capacity of the tank or how much the tanks holds = 16 + 8 = <<16+8=24>>24 gallons
